comments.body:
I don't like the lingering (and overly general) method, what if we added it inside the test to minimize scope as a const lambda instead?
And the `while` loop is basically a `for` loop in disguise:
```C++
const auto compute_depth{[](const NodeU32& node) {
    size_t depth{0};
    for (const auto* n{&node}; !n->Subs().empty(); n = &n->Subs().front()) {
        ++depth;
    }
    return depth;
}};
```

